real_commentary: KICKOFF:  France kick off, and we are under way in Dusseldorf!
our_sequence_commentary: [Kick Off] The Round of 16 match begins. France versus Belgium underway!

real_commentary: Early on, France put a half-chance wide, as Rabiot prods the ball several yards to the left of Casteels' goal. It was a tough volley to execute, in all fairness to the Juventus midfielder.
our_sequence_commentary: [Shot Missed] Attempt missed. Adrien Rabiot's left footed shot from the centre of the box goes over the bar.

real_commentary: Interestingly, six players that started the 2018 World Cup semi-final between these nations also start in Germany today: Mbappe, Kante and Griezmann for France; De Bruyne, Lukaku and Vertonghen for Belgium.
our_sequence_commentary: [Foul] Foul by Adrien Rabiot (France) on Wout Faes (Belgium). Free kick awarded in midfield.

real_commentary: France are enjoying their first sustained spell of pressure, but it all dies out when Thuram tries to win a free kick from Theate on the right byline and his claims are quickly dismissed by the referee.
our_sequence_commentary: [General] Belgium firmly in control early on, dominating possession with 96.1%.

real_commentary: This is just the second time Openda and Lukaku have started together for their national team, and it seems a curious point of the tournament to experiment. Will Tedesco's tinkering pay off, though?
our_sequence_commentary: [General] France continues to dominate, 78.5% possession, Tchouaméni influential in midfield.

real_commentary: Allowed to travel through midfield and towards the edge of Belgium's area, Griezmann eyes up a shot. However, his 20-yard effort is sent bobbling low along the turf, and Casteels comfortably gathers it.
our_sequence_commentary: [Shot Saved] Attempt saved. Antoine Griezmann's left footed shot from the edge of the box denied by Koen Casteels.

real_commentary: Griezmann and Kounde cleverly combine on the right flank, and the ball is cut back into the box by the latter, only to evade every French player. A real moment of concern for the Belgians there.
our_sequence_commentary: [General] France dominating, holding 100% possession in the attacking third for two minutes. Jules Koundé heavily involved with seven events.

real_commentary: After Hernandez lays a short pass off to Mbappe on the left side of the area, the France captain lashes an angled shot towards goal. It takes a deflection and flies wide, but the referee somehow misses the Belgian defender's touch and awards a goal kick instead.
our_sequence_commentary: [Yellow Card] Aurélien Tchouaméni (France) receives a yellow card for a foul.

real_commentary: YELLOW CARD!  After France are mistakenly denied a corner kick, Tchouameni protests a little too long and too loudly, so he receives the game's first booking. He'll have to tread carefully from now on.
our_sequence_commentary: [General] Belgium in complete control with 91% possession, France struggling to break through.

real_commentary: CHANCE!  France continue to press for an opening goal: Thuram arrives in front of his marker at the near post, only to steer a header from Griezmann's corner well wide of the target.
our_sequence_commentary: [General] France in complete control, dominating midfield for the last two minutes. Upamecano heavily involved with six key contributions.

real_commentary: It's quite surprising just how passively Belgium have started this match, perhaps paying their old rivals a little bit too much respect. They've barely laid a glove on Les Bleus thus far.
our_sequence_commentary: [General] France dominating possession with 100%, controlling midfield effectively. Tchouaméni leading with 12 events.

real_commentary: With a wildly optimistic effort, Rabiot thumps a 30-yarder high and wide of the target. There was no pressure on the ball, so he felt entitled to have a go - surely the wrong option, though.
our_sequence_commentary: [Shot Missed] Attempt missed. Adrien Rabiot's left footed shot from the edge of the box goes over the bar.

real_commentary: YELLOW CARD!  Doku jinks in from the left, driving towards the edge of the area. With Kounde caught on his heels, Griezmann drops back to help out and clips the Manchester City winger. That's a booking - and a rather harsh one.
our_sequence_commentary: [General] Belgium firmly in control, dominating midfield with 100% possession. Jan Vertonghen leading the charge with 9 events.

real_commentary: SAVE!  From a free kick on the left side of the box, De Bruyne curls the ball towards the centre of the goal. Maignan sees it late, then scrambles it away to safety with a very unorthodox stop! He hacks it away with his legs!
our_sequence_commentary: [Yellow Card] Adrien Rabiot (France) shown a yellow card for a foul on Jeremy Doku (Belgium).

real_commentary: SAVE!  From a free kick on the left side of the box, De Bruyne curls the ball towards the centre of the goal. Maignan sees it late, then scrambles it away to safety with a very unorthodox stop! He hacks it away with his legs!
our_sequence_commentary: [Injury] Injury concern for Belgium as Jeremy Doku goes down, receiving treatment.

real_commentary: A pause in play for an injury to Doku allows both managers to give out some tactical instruction, and the players take on drinks, too. Fortunately, the Belgian winger is ultimately fit enough to return.
our_sequence_commentary: [Foul] Foul by Adrien Rabiot (France) on Kevin De Bruyne (Belgium) in midfield.

real_commentary: Carrasco has a volleyed shot blocked in the box, and there's no doubt that the Belgium have brightened up over the past 10 minutes or so. It had been a rather subdued start from the Red Devils.
our_sequence_commentary: [General] Belgium dominating possession with 89.1%, controlling the midfield. Jan Vertonghen heavily involved.

real_commentary: France have had 58% of the ball so far, which demonstrates just how much they were on top in the early stages. It's developing into a much more even affair now, though.
our_sequence_commentary: [Foul] Foul by Loïs Openda (Belgium) on Mike Maignan (France) in the defensive half.

real_commentary: A pretty woeful cross from the left by Hernandez sails straight over the byline and out for a goal kick to Belgium. For all their possession, Les Bleus have produced just one shot on target today.
our_sequence_commentary: [General] France in control with 61% possession, dominating midfield for 2 minutes. Theo Hernández highly active.

real_commentary: CLOSE!  Again, Kounde advances down the right, and he delivers a dangerous ball to the near post. Thuram arrives to meet it with a well-timed leap, but his header zips narrowly wide of the right-hand post!
our_sequence_commentary: [Shot Missed] Attempt missed. Marcus Thuram heads the ball over from the center of the box.

real_commentary: CLOSE!  At the end of a long French build-up, Tchouameni spots a chance to shoot from mid-range, but his power-packed effort rises just over the top-right corner.
our_sequence_commentary: [Shot Missed] Attempt missed. Aurélien Tchouaméni's right footed shot from the edge of the box goes wide.

real_commentary: France are now totally on top in Dusseldorf, where Belgium have again dropped deep. Even Openda and Lukaku are back inside their defensive third - they're all chasing shadows at the moment.
our_sequence_commentary: [Shot Missed] Attempt missed. Marcus Thuram's right footed shot from the six yard box goes wide.

real_commentary: Thuram just can't reach the ball when Griezmann ends another clever passage of play by clipping a cute pass over the top. Casteels claims it, but Belgium are merely hanging on for half time here.
our_sequence_commentary: [Injury] Kylian Mbappé Lottin (France) down with an injury, concerns for the French side.

real_commentary: HALF TIME:  FRANCE 0-0 BELGIUM
our_sequence_commentary: [Corner] Corner for France, delivered by Antoine Griezmann. Conceded by Wout Faes.

real_commentary: As France continue penning their opponents in, the officials indicate that just one minute of first-half stoppage time will be played.
our_sequence_commentary: [Corner] Corner for France, delivered by Antoine Griezmann. Conceded by Wout Faes.

real_commentary: CLOSE!  Right at the end of the half, Tchouameni again misses the target. Following persistent play by Mbappe on the left flank, the ball falls nicely for his new Real Madrid teammate; however, the subsequent shot is drilled about three feet over the top.
our_sequence_commentary: [Shot Missed] Attempt missed. Aurélien Tchouaméni's right footed shot from the centre of the box goes wide.

real_commentary: KICKOFF:  No personnel changes for either side during half time, and Belgium get us back under way in Dusseldorf.
our_sequence_commentary: [Kick Off] The second half is underway. Round of 16, France vs. Belgium.

real_commentary: SAVE!  Tchouameni tries his luck again, but Casteels is equal to it! The midfielder's dominant display continues, following a fine first half, as he strides forward and curls a shot towards the bottom-right corner: Belgium's goalkeeper tips it away!
our_sequence_commentary: [General] France dominating midfield once again, holding 67% possession and dictating play.

real_commentary: CHANCE!  After an underwhelming set-piece situation, France recover the ball and then deliver it from the left towards Thuram at the near post. Again, the Inter Milan striker fails to connect correctly, and it comes off the top of his shoulder before flying well over the crossbar.
our_sequence_commentary: [Shots] France applying pressure with two attempts. Kylian Mbappé's shot blocked, Thuram's header off target.

real_commentary: It's 'as you were', then. France have resumed their dominance of both ball and territory since half time, with Belgium meekly sitting back and vainly hoping to strike on the break.
our_sequence_commentary: [General] France dominating possession with 94.8%, controlling the midfield effectively.

real_commentary: CLOSE!  Mbappe almost breaks the deadlock! The France captain weaves in from the left at top speed, leaving several defenders in his wake, but his dipping shot zips narrowly over the crossbar! Brilliant stuff from Les Bleus' skipper!
our_sequence_commentary: [Shot Missed] Attempt missed. Kylian Mbappé's right footed shot from the center of the box goes over the target.

real_commentary: Not for the first time, Kounde advances to the right edge of the area, and his ball sets up Mbappe. However, the latter can't control his shot, which skips well wide of the left-hand post.
our_sequence_commentary: [Shot Missed] Attempt missed. Kylian Mbappé's right footed shot from the centre of the box goes wide.

real_commentary: Somehow, Doku extracts himself from a sticky situation: penned into the corner, near his own area, the winger's fleet footwork buys a free kick off Kounde. He took a risk there, but it payed off.
our_sequence_commentary: [Foul] Foul by Jules Koundé (France) on Jeremy Doku (Belgium) in the defensive half.

real_commentary: At the traditional hour mark, the time seems ripe for some substitutions. None appear to be on their way just yet, but Tedesco must surely be thinking of some changes; Deschamps, too.
our_sequence_commentary: [Foul] Foul by Amadou Onana (Belgium) on Kylian Mbappé Lottin (France) in midfield.

real_commentary: CHANCE!  AC Milan teammates Hernandez and Maignan celebrate as if they've just scored a goal, as Carrasco is denied a chance to shoot from close range when played through by De Bruyne. It was good defending, but the shot needed to be taken sooner.
our_sequence_commentary: [Shot Blocked] Attempt blocked. Yannick Ferreira Carrasco's right footed shot denied by Theo Hernández.

real_commentary: FRANCE SUB: Deschamps decides to shuffle his forward line, as Thuram departs and Kolo Muani comes on.
our_sequence_commentary: [Substitution] Substitution for France. Randal Kolo Muani replaces Marcus Thuram.

real_commentary: BELGIUM SUB: Tedesco responds by sending on Mangala for Openda. Surely that'll release De Bruyne to do his stuff further up the pitch.
our_sequence_commentary: [Substitution] Substitution for Belgium. Orel Mangala replaces Loïs Openda in a tactical change.

real_commentary: France flood forward again: this time, Griezmann latches onto a pass and pulls his low shot wide of the right-hand post.
our_sequence_commentary: [Shot Missed] Attempt missed. Antoine Griezmann's right footed shot from the edge of the box goes off target.

real_commentary: It growing ever more tense in Dusseldorf, where the one-way traffic continues. Can Belgium find a way to halt the French tide and start creating some of their own chances?
our_sequence_commentary: [General] Belgium dominating midfield with 74.5% possession, controlling play for 2 minutes.

real_commentary: CLOSE!  Tchouameni shoots over again, following fine build-up play from Mbappe and Griezmann. This time, the ball is fired narrowly off target from around 20 yards out.
our_sequence_commentary: [Shot Missed] Attempt missed. Aurélien Tchouaméni's right footed shot from the edge of the box goes wide.

real_commentary: SAVE!  Lukaku denied! Belgium almost snatch the lead, against the run of play! Mangala bursts down the left, then cuts the ball back for the Red Devils' record scorer; Lukaku shoots low and hard but Maignan is equal to it!
our_sequence_commentary: [Injury] Jan Vertonghen (Belgium) down, receiving treatment on the pitch.

real_commentary: SAVE!  Lukaku denied! Belgium almost snatch the lead, against the run of play! Mangala bursts down the left, then cuts the ball back for the Red Devils' record scorer; Lukaku shoots low and hard but Maignan is equal to it!
our_sequence_commentary: [Injury] Kylian Mbappé Lottin (France) down with an injury, play halted.

real_commentary: Penalties and own goals excluded, France haven't scored with any of their 63 shots at Euro 2024 so far. The frustration must be immense for fans of Les Bleus.
our_sequence_commentary: [General] France dominating play, controlling possession for the last two minutes. Tchouaméni highly involved.

real_commentary: CLOSE!  Saliba shows great skill to evade Doku in the Belgian area, then lines up a shot. However, he becomes the latest French player to spurn a half-chance, shooting over from 15 yards.
our_sequence_commentary: [Shot Missed] Attempt missed. William Saliba's left-footed shot from the centre of the box goes off target. France pressing hard with 11 corners to Belgium's 4 in this

real_commentary: YELLOW CARD!  After getting entangled with Kolo Muani by the touchline, Vertonghen is shown a yellow card by the referee. For his subsequent complaints, Tedesco joins his defender in the book.
our_sequence_commentary: [Yellow Card] Jan Vertonghen (Belgium) shown a yellow card for a late challenge.

real_commentary: CLOSE!  Mbappe comes ever so close once again! He curls a first-time strike narrowly over the crossbar from just inside the area. Belgium can breathe again!
our_sequence_commentary: [Shot Missed] Attempt missed. Kylian Mbappé's right footed shot from the center of the box goes over the target.

real_commentary: Both coaches have made just one change so far. Surely it's time to go for broke? Or are we ambling towards extra time in Dusseldorf?
our_sequence_commentary: [General] France dominating midfield with 100% possession, Tchouaméni the standout performer.

real_commentary: SAVE!  Good stop from Maignan! Lukaku holds the ball up well, then Doku flicks it through to the on-rushing De Bruyne to shoot. He hits it hard and true from the edge of the box, but France's number one makes an important save!
our_sequence_commentary: [Foul] Foul by N'Golo Kanté (France) on Jeremy Doku (Belgium). Free kick awarded near the left side of the box.

real_commentary: GOAL!  France go in front! Just when it seemed they were all out of ideas! At the end of a smart passing move, Kante picks out Kolo Muani on the right side of the area, and the latter's shot is deflected past Casteels and into the back of the net! Vertonghen is the unlucky man, adding his name to several with own goals at Euro 2024.
our_sequence_commentary: [Shot Missed] Attempt missed. Randal Kolo Muani's right footed shot from the centre of the box goes wide.

real_commentary: GOAL!  FRANCE 1-0 BELGIUM (VERTONGHEN OWN GOAL)
our_sequence_commentary: [Shot Missed] Attempt missed. Randal Kolo Muani's right footed shot from the centre of the box goes wide.

real_commentary: Les Bleus lead. Can Belgium respond, or is it too late? They've really got to switch momentum now - and fast.
our_sequence_commentary: [General] Belgium dominating midfield with 85% possession, controlling play for the last 2 minutes.

real_commentary: BELGIUM SUBS: On come De Ketelaere and Lukebakio; Castagne and Carrasco are hauled off. It's all or nothing now!
our_sequence_commentary: [Substitution] Double change for Belgium. Timothy Castagne off, Charles De Ketelaere on. Yannick Ferreira Carrasco also replaces another teammate.

real_commentary: BELGIUM SUBS: On come De Ketelaere and Lukebakio; Castagne and Carrasco are hauled off. It's all or nothing now!
our_sequence_commentary: [Substitution] Double change for Belgium. Dodi Lukebakio replaces Yannick Ferreira Carrasco, and Thomas Meunier comes on for Timothy Castagne.

real_commentary: Theate tries to drive the ball into the box, but summing up Belgium's day, it strikes the referee and all momentum is lost.
our_sequence_commentary: [Injury] Jan Vertonghen (Belgium) down with an injury. Medical staff attending to him.

real_commentary: In the second minute of at least three added for stoppages, Belgium are flooding forward in numbers. For the first time, France are on the back foot. Will Les Bleus see this out?
our_sequence_commentary: [General] Belgium dominating midfield, controlling possession for the last two minutes. Orel Mangala leading the charge.

real_commentary: FULL TIME:  FRANCE 1-0 BELGIUM
our_sequence_commentary: [General] Belgium in total control with 100% possession as stoppage time progresses.
